A song from the album has even made it to the radio hit - the mr2 Petőfi, who has been broadcasting pop music from early to late since the very latest, has gradually made the listener's attention with the number "Wings of Love", which was recorded with the participation of six local singers ("Underground Divas").
Everything's all right, then (?).
The hvg.hu asked Balázs Zságer.
hvg.hu: This new hit raises the question: To what extent is your music reserved for a certain layer?
Balázs Zságer: The term "shift music" does not mean much to me.
In my opinion, there are two boxes in pop music, not mainstream and underground, or alternative and pop, but commercial and honest.
Even the so-called alternative or underground music can be shallow and meaningless, but also they can only be produced for the sale that makes them commercial music.
A good pop number can also come from an honest motive.
The listener's willingness to record also works according to this principle, independent of languages and national borders.
hvg.hu: Do you see a difference in the openness of the Hungarian and foreign audiences to your music?
B. Zs.: In foreign countries, especially to the west of us, pop music has a greater tradition.
There are not only teenagers or Twens going to concerts, but also the older audience.
They follow the trends in pop music that are happening around them much more attentively, because they also consider it a part of contemporary culture.
hvg.hu: What role does the audience play in your work?
Is it important who, where, how many listen to your music?
B. Zs.: Of course it is a good feeling to see that more and more come to our concerts.
But we never composed for the market.
We do not create music to serve a purpose, but for a certain reason.
The role of the audience is usually noticeable at the concerts, where there is already a mutual interaction, but these in turn exist only in the incomprehensible changes of the moment.
Still, I noticed that if you want to make it right for everyone, you're no longer interesting.
hvg.hu: How far do you want to follow the example of Yonderboi?
He is on the road as a soloist and has built his career more in the West.
B. Zs.: We don’t really go his way, not to mention that we try to interpret this into our music time and again.
We see ourselves as team players who rely on each other's musical presence and let them unfold.
At first, of course, comparisons of our work with that of Yonderboi were inevitable, as several of us came out of his band and took a different path.
hvg.hu: In the charts of mr2 Petőfi "Wings of Love" comes first.
Many have only heard the name Zagar in connection with this number.
Was the opening consciously staged with a somewhat more popular style towards a wider audience?
B. Zs.: We didn't have any plans to write a hit, which should then be used as a draw horse for the album.
This song is about more.
It was intended as the finale of the album, with which we wanted to dissolve the sound orgy and the somewhat more difficult themes.
hvg.hu: How did you choose the six singers?
Why them, what was the guiding principle?
B. Zs.: The basic idea was to make a gospel-like choir.
Then came the idea of putting together the choir of talented soloists from the local music scene.
This is how the six-member choir was created - that is, Sena, Edina Kutzora, Judie Jay, Bori Péterfy, Enikő Hodosi [Neo], Juci Németh - which we then baptized apater "Underground Divas".
hvg.hu: Did you want the song the same way, or did the girls shape it?
B. Zs.: The number has been in the instrumental version for a long time, but when the material for the album was ready, we thought that this number still "needs something".
The chord sequence has formally demanded a vocal voice.
I sang the melody the same night, later they learned the girls.
It all came practically right at the start and frighteningly spontaneous.
I can remember, I was quite electrified at the time, but it was already necessary for the "divas".
With my voice alone, the song would never have become so strong.
hvg.hu: Both on the record and at the concert you had the impression that the girls were in the background.
There is no solo part (apart from Judy Jay's short solo), they have no role of their own, sing together completely and are not louder than the music, so their singing is not only accompanied by the music.
They were also on stage in the back.
Is it on purpose?
B.Zs.: The fact that they stood in the back was due to purely technical problems.
However, we deliberately did not want to give them solo roles.
In the number it is also a matter of forgetting one's ego a little, forgetting who has come from and where to go, we simply allow these particular wings, the wings of love, to lift us up.
I would like others to feel this euphoric state that we felt when the song came into being.
hvg.hu: What was the most elaborate song?
B. Zs.: In the musical work actually none, there were more difficult tasks when mixing.
For example, in "Dorian Gray's Dilemma", in which I play on a concert piano, or in "Rock'n'Roll Goes To The Girls", where the groove didn't want to work for a while, but gradually everything came together, like in a puzzle.
hvg.hu: What is your favorite number from the new album?
B. Zs.: This is constantly changing with the concerts and even now that I have left the album "lost".
Currently it is "Prophet Is A Fool", "Escape From The Earth" and the number "Never The Same".
