Czech ministers and representatives of the European Commission signed a total of nine development programmes yesterday, which will allow the Czech Republic to reach EUR 14 billion in the next few years (approximately CZK 365 billion).
It is about half of the amount that the Czech Republic can receive from Brussels in the years 2007 to 2013.
About 125 billion kroner come from seven regional development programmes.
Czech companies will be able to receive about 100 billion kroner from the "Business and Innovation" programme.
