This money will increase according to the budget of the State Transport Infrastructure Fund, which will have 90.8 billion next year.
The "Enterprise and Innovation" programme is intended to help entrepreneurs and companies to attract funds to innovative enterprises.
The aim is to raise finance for the introduction of new technologies, for corporate research, but also for the introduction of more effective organisational methods.
The Czech Republic is among the least successful among the new candidate countries in the past acquisition of money from EU funds.
