A daring exit that, due to its duration, the removal of habitable modules, the speed with which it was organized, and the tools made by astronauts to carry out the repair, has achieved several records.
The problem occurred on Wednesday, when the astronauts had unloaded the Harmony module from the Discovery space shuttle, a large cylindrical part that will soon take up the European and Japanese scientific laboratories.
This module is a kind of landing bridge for the module laboratories.
But you have to be able to power them.
The second task of the crew was to implement a 17.5-ton module for power generation via solar panels, which was already on the ISS, in order to put it in its final position.
