And it happened that one of the collectors that can be folded up like accordions was damaged by a jammed cable on a length of about one meter.
The restructuring was stopped in order not to damage the collector any more.
The astronauts, who were originally to leave the space shuttle Discovery for a control passage and then repair another solar collector whose rotation system was faulty, were forced to devote themselves to the damaged collector.
And Scott Parazynski was chosen to walk around at the end of the 30 meter long remote-controlled arm of the space shuttle that had been attached to the station to carry out repair.
He is one of NASA's best spacewalkers.
Large, resistant, very skillful, he has a well developed torso and long arms.
The 46-year-old doctor was selected to operate the injured solar collector.
