He was supported by a second spacewalker who remained near the lock, and, from inside, by the other astronauts, among them Peggy Whitson, commander of the crew.
The tool he used, a mini-hockey bat, wrapped with an insulator to prevent an electric blow on the solar panels that produce several hundred volts, the astronauts on board the station had designed and made.
