Which insurance is best for me?
The motor vehicle insurance, which covers a possible case of damage caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which again depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of issue of the driving licence, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even harder to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, it must be clear what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and a policyholder.
This agreement shall be recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract which determines that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and in return is obliged to present the corresponding compensation amount in the event of a claim.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance which is composed of several factors, including age, sex, date of issue of the driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that higher contributions are also due in the event of a higher risk of accidents.
For this reason, both over 25 and women have to pay less contributions, as statistics show that, thanks to their caution, these groups have a lower accident rate.
The same applies to married persons, who, according to the statistics and therefore also according to the firm's conviction, tend to have fewer accidents than single persons.
The benefit attributed to the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and thus also the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting the premium, insurance companies must take account of a number of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to choose exactly the car insurance that best suits his personal needs.
We now list the most important points that should be considered when choosing an insurance policy in order to be able to make not only a performance but also a price-oriented choice.
The under-25s encounter numerous obstacles when choosing low-cost insurance, such as low driving practice and the young driver's license.
Even if it would be best to take out comprehensive insurance for an ideal insurance cover, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The careful drivers can choose a fully self-employed driver, so that the benefits of a comprehensive insurance are covered but offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer must pay part of the amount incurred by the damage himself.
The amount is determined before the conclusion of the contract and based on the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, Spain's main representative at First Europa, an online insurance broker.
Another option is the extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused to his own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you are under 25 years old, it is in your hands to reduce insurance costs; so your credit is increased by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate of the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in the tariff.
The amount of credits and penalties depends on the company and its income.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it may be possible to increase the bonus payments, explains Noguera.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to sign a contract. This is due to the fact that the accident rate decreases with increasing driving practice.
Thus, it is most appropriate to opt for a fully comprehensive insurance with a deductible.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish head of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the fear of the beginner has been abandoned.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable for a married customer who does not have children to take full insurance; of course, only if the financial situation of the person concerned allows it.
On the part of insurers, couples with children are considered to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and accordingly, their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, the best option would be a comprehensive insurance with a deductible (with an amount of around 300 euros). In the case of a high credit, it is recommended that an extended insurance, which does not start until the third year of the vehicle.
They drive more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power, which allows them to set a higher contribution payment, Luis Noguera notes.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out a comprehensive insurance with a deductible (for an amount of around 150 euros) or an extended insurance, which only applies with a sufficiently high credit.
In the end, it is important to note that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver against possible accident damage, but also because it entails high costs, which require a thorough selection to be made that corresponds to our personal situation.
